# Alaya Agent Working Contract

Hard stops from Codex/Claude memories and Alaya sessions. Complements
`AGENTS.md` and do-it; skills/hooks are advisory — these bind.

## 1. Goal before craft

- Name the user's gate/metric/outcome in one sentence before editing.
- Prefer the critical path over adjacent plumbing. Missing the gate is Spec
  failure even if the craft is clean.
- Do not retune weights/caps/cutoffs against bench matrix deltas (anti-fitting).
- Pre-launch: do not invent user/compat constraints unless asked.
- Prefer root-cause over speculative blame of externals/models; study OUR code
  (and SOTA) first.

## 2. No silent product semantics

Product decisions (not "plumbing"): retrieval/FTS/fusion/delivery defaults,
Garden grounding, embedding availability, trust keys, MCP shapes.

Cite an existing decision or get an explicit call before changing defaults or
memory formation. Flag-gated "intended" features left forever-off are dead
code — either default them with proof or delete; "wired" ≠ "default-on".

## 3. Honest claims only

| Claim | Means |
| --- | --- |
| implemented | code+tests on this worktree |
| matrix/gate passed | fresh run proves the named KPI |
| ready to merge/push | verify + review + intended diff; full typecheck/test when pushing |

- Never collapse these. `IMPLEMENTATION_CLEAN` ≠ gate passed. Green build ≠
  lifecycle/runtime closed.
- Re-check prior findings against live code; classify `fixed` / `stale` /
  `overclaimed` / backlog — do not implement stale prose.
- SLIs measure what they claim. Retrieval fail-open that hides empty hits is a
  measurement lie. Cover-ups (empty catch, weakened tests, fixture edits) are
  defects.
- Trust live `git` / files over GitNexus when they conflict. Advisory hooks ≠
  hard enforcement; validators ≠ tracked delivery completeness.

## 4. Mode and artifact discipline

- `先不写代码` / planning-only → update `.do-it` artifacts; do not edit source.
- `只读验收` / `不要修改文件` → verdict only: Blocking/Important + evidence +
  explicit `NOT_CHECKED`; no repair drift.
- When the user points at a report/plan/findings file, that artifact is the
  acceptance checklist.
- If asked to list workers, put actual subagent/lane list at the top.
- Optimize for minimal prompt ceremony and high execution quality.
- Prefer `rtk`-prefixed commands; if the wrapper blocks inspection, use a
  wrapper-safe variant rather than inventing raw flags.

## 5. Source hygiene

```ts
// ❌ // G3 deep head / G5 coverage may reorder vs fused_rank
// ✅ // Lexical family must not override independent embedding dominance.
```

Why-not-what only; one terse line. No ticket/wave/item IDs, experiment labels,
or sales-pitch design comments. One reason to change per module; reuse before
repeat; respect AGENTS.md size/phase limits. New tests: prefer real
better-sqlite3 over mock soup.

## 6. Multi-agent / worktree / review

- Edit only the named worktree. Parallel waves → one branch per worktree from
  fresh main; parent owns integration. Do not edit read-only benchmark trees.
- Do not commit/push/merge/delete branches unless explicitly asked (or the user
  already authorized that closeout).
- Subagents: goal + ownership + closing evidence. Do not abort a mid-edit
  worker on transient diagnostics — review products when the lane finishes.
- Honor model allow-lists. Parent keeps final judgment; worker summaries are
  not closeout proof.
- Review/fix-loop: Nice-to-have findings must also be fixed before closeout
  (rerun reviewer only if that fix expands scope/behavior/risk). Fix
  pre-existing nits in remediation passes — do not defer as out-of-scope.
  Blocking/Important still need a fresh reviewer pass.
